{
  "article_id": "StLouisRepublic1893",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "One of the strange true tales of modern life is that of ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman Robinson Crusoe",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the \"Wild Woman,\"",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "as she was locally but improperly called, who lived alone for 17 years on ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas Island",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", a small and rocky bit of land just off the ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "California Coast",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", near ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_la",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The Californian Magazine in its October number prints some particulars never before made known of this woman's lonely life, and of these, by the courtesy of the Eastern agents of the Californian, the New York Recorder presents a condensed account:"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "If we could form a mental picture of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "as it appeared a half century ago, we should find its physical features the same as those which it presents to-day—a rocky, wave-beaten finger-tip of nature peeping above the surface of the Pacific nearly due southwest of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles",
        "entity_key": "ci_la",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", moss-carpeted where the brushwood has found no soil wherein to take root, and rising in the center so as to form a hill with somewhat steep declivities. We should perceive at the base of this eminence springs of fresh water which would supply the unfortunate mariner who might have the ill-luck to be cast away on that uninviting shore. Wild dogs would be seen roaming about or stealthily creeping up to the seals that lay basking in the sun and slumbering on the craggy rocks and beach, while shags perched on peaks and slabs plume their oily feathers in the warm rays. The twittering of small birds in the brush might also form part of this mental impression. A close scrutiny would reveal on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the mainland",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "side of the hill three small brushwood huts, with frameworks of the bones of the whale, and a low brush fence before them as a wind-break. In front of one of these lowly huts would be seen a woman squatted on the ground engaged in weaving a water vessel or bottle, her textile material being grass fiber, of which she had an abundance at hand, collected from the margins of springs and the moist, swampy patches, which occupy the nooks and recesses of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "THE story of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Wild Woman of San Nicolas Island",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "is a singular one. Outlines and summaries of it have been published from time to time, but a full account has never been given, nor has any part of it been presented as related by "
      },
      {
        "text": "the principal actors",
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "cdi"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "engaged in her rescue after she had lived in solitude for 17 years on "
      },
      {
        "text": "that lonely isle",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". That it can be so given now is due to the zeal and thoughtfulness of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. D. W. Thompson",
        "entity_key": "dth",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", one of the fathers of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "City of Flowers",
        "entity_key": "ci_la",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and to him we are indebted for a decidedly curious page of history. In 1882, "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Thompson",
        "entity_key": "dth",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", accompanied by "
      },
      {
        "text": "a shorthand reporter",
        "entity_key": "reporter4",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", sought out those "
      },
      {
        "text": "principal actors",
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "cdi"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "—the venerable pioneers, "
      },
      {
        "text": "George Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Charles Brown",
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "—and by elaborate questioning obtained full particulars connected with the unfortunate woman's career."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "It is conjectured by "
      },
      {
        "text": "those pioneers",
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "cdi"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "that all the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara Islands",
        "entity_key": "i_northernchi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "were settled by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Indians",
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who, according to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Brown",
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", were much molested by "
      },
      {
        "text": "the tribes from the Northwest",
        "entity_keys": [
          "rfurcompany",
          "iba",
          "natam_aleuts",
          "natam_kodiak",
          "1814huntingparty"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "These warlike savages",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "rfurcompany",
          "iba",
          "natam_aleuts",
          "natam_kodiak",
          "1814huntingparty"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "would cross the channel in their canoes, and hunt and shoot ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the poor islanders",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "\"just for mischief.\"",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Whatever may have been the reason for adopting such a measure, "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Mexican Government",
        "entity_key": "gov_mexico",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "informs us, decided to remove "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "dwelling on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the mainland",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and distribute them among "
      },
      {
        "text": "the missions",
        "entity_key": "mi_mainlandmissions",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The small schooner",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "sent by "
      },
      {
        "text": "the authorities",
        "entity_key": "misfats",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "to bring off "
      },
      {
        "text": "the last family",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", which consisted of seven or eight members, was called "
      },
      {
        "text": "Better-Than-Nothing",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "and was in command of an old sea otter hunter named "
      },
      {
        "text": "Sparks",
        "entity_key": "isp",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". They succeeded in getting all on board except "
      },
      {
        "text": "two children",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "who, though brought down to the beach, was so distracted at her "
      },
      {
        "text": "two children",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "having been left behind that they let her go back and sailed away."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "IT is not difficult to picture to one's self the condition and miseries of "
      },
      {
        "text": "this lonely woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", separated from "
      },
      {
        "text": "her husband",
        "entity_key": "lwhusband",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and family and dependent on herself for every necessity of life. We can see her day by day gazing seaward, on the watch for "
      },
      {
        "text": "the boat",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The days summed up into months and months grew into years, but no schooner returned. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Her children",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "meanwhile had been devoured by wild dogs. She saw ships going by, this way and that, but nobody came for her. Her cry of \"Manequauna!\" was unheeded, and as time lapsed she became adapted to circumstances and her surroundings. With deft fingers she wove baskets and water-tight vessels, smearing the latter with melted asphaltum; she twisted the sinews of seals, which she caught while sleeping, into fishing lines; she dug up the succulent roots of plants and roasted them over fire obtained by rubbing two sticks together; and clothed herself in sea bird skins, which she sewed together with fine sinew with the aid of needles made of bone. "
      },
      {
        "text": "As the years passed by she became contented with her lot; time dulled her grief, and she accepted the situation with the stoical resignation of her race.",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Fish, seal flesh and roots formed her diet; pure spring water was her only beverage. Once she fel[l] deadly sick, lying helpless on the ground for days before she recovered. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Pioneer Brown",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ],
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "sa[y]s: \"She made signs that she had been sick, lying in the dirt for days. She coul[d] not move; all alone, she was down sick and got well.\"",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "But the day arrived when the white man again interfered with the current of her life, and with fatal result. The time came at last when she was to leave "
      },
      {
        "text": "her island home",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", [sic] It seems to have been suspected, if not confidently understood, that "
      },
      {
        "text": "a wild woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was living on "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", for "
      },
      {
        "text": "Padre Gonzales",
        "entity_key": "jru",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "requested "
      },
      {
        "text": "Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "to search for her. \"I went over three times,\" he says, \"before I found her.\""
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Brown",
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "is more circumstantial in his account. "
      },
      {
        "text": "He says:",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "\"I went round the head of ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and found tracks of ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "; went back and told ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the old gentleman",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "that ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was alive. He said it must be some of ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "our Indians",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". I said: '",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Our Indians",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "have got bigger tracks than that.' He said: 'Well, if you think she is alive let us hunt for her, and take ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "all the men",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "ashore.' We went up to the head of ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". There was a kind of hill in the middle. I put ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "my Indians",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "a couple of hundred yards apart. I did not know what kind of woman she was; thought she might bite or scratch. We went from one side of ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "to the other, and could not see the hill, and she was sitting on the side of the hill watching us. When we got across to ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "I said: 'There's nothing here, let's go back.' There was a basket with some feathers. She caught shags and had a coat made without sleeves, nicely covered with sealskin. I said to ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ": 'You go to the hill and scatter the feathers and things in the basket, and if she is alive she will find them.' The same day we found them all gathered up again and put in the basket.\"",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "On the following morning ",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Brown",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ],
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "persistently continued the hunt. Toiling up the hill, when he was about half way up, he caught sight of her. She was carrying something heavy and rested at intervals as she ascended. Presently he came in sight of \"three huts\" made out of whalebone. Here he expected to find her, but, peering in, found that she was not there. Presently he espied \"something like a crow sitting on a whalebone,\" and perceiving that it was ",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman he was in search of",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", he raised his gun with his hat on it as a signal to ",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", whom he hastily summoned, as he did not know if she would \"bite or scratch.\"",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "\"She had a brush fence about 2 feet high to break the wind, and right in front of me she sat, facing me.",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The sun was coming in her face. She was skinning a seal before I came up to her. The dog, when he noticed me, began to growl. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Thinking she might run, I stepped round her, and she bowed as if she knew me before, and when ",
        "tropes": [
          1,
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "tropes": [
          1,
          3
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "came up they all kneeled.\" ",
        "tropes": [
          1,
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The poor creature",
        "tropes": [
          1,
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", when she saw beings of her own color and race, \"hold out some of her food\" to them.",
        "tropes": [
          1,
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "She exhibited no fear, and at a sign went without demur with "
      },
      {
        "text": "her captors",
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "cdi",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "Brown",
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "his followers",
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "carried away with them all her primitive belongings. \"I took everything she had,\" he says, \"and she took a big seal head in her basket, and that was all. We all had something to carry.\" Arriving at a watering place \"she washed herself over. Her hair was all rotting away, and kind of bleached by the sun.\" When they reached "
      },
      {
        "text": "the vessel",
        "entity_key": "sh_nidever",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "she kneeled and crawled to the stove which was on deck. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Brown",
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "gave her some biscuit, which she enjoyed, and made petticoats and skirts for her out of bedticking and sailors' clothes."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "When ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Wild Woman",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "reached ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "all ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her family",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "were dead. They had been taken to ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Pedro",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sp",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", where they pined and died.",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The priests",
        "entity_keys": [
          "jru",
          "aji",
          "sanchez",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "tried hard to g[e]t her life's story from her, but her gibberish was unintelligible. Indians were brought to her from "
      },
      {
        "text": "Ventura",
        "entity_key": "ci_ven",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and other places, but they could only understand a few words spoken by her. Finally "
      },
      {
        "text": "an old woman",
        "entity_key": "natamwoman1",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "who had been raised on one of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "was found who could understand what she said to a limited extent."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "At the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mission of Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "mi_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "the Wild Woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was baptised under the Christian name of Juana Maria, as "
      },
      {
        "text": "Brown",
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "thinks, though not feeling certain on that point. From one of the men who had sailed in "
      },
      {
        "text": "the little schooner Better-Than-Nothing",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ", she received the name of "
      },
      {
        "text": "that vessel",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Says ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ": \"She would go round to different homes and dance Indian dances. She went all over ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "town",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the mission",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "mi_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", always a party of 20 or 30 Indians and Mexicans with her.\" ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Brown",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "corroborates this testimony as to her contentment: \"Happy as a lady. She would dance when anyone came in.\" Clothes were her especial delight.",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was a great curiosity, and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who had taken her into his house, was offered $1,000 to part with her, the object of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the would-be purchaser",
        "entity_key": "tru",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "being to exhibit her. To his lasting honor he refused to make such a bargain, because \"it did not look right to me to sell a person.\""
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "BUT the end was drawing near. Change of diet cut short the life of the luckless ",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Juana Maria",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who would doubtless have lived many years longer had she been allowed to remain in ",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her island home",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", or even if due caution had been taken with regard to what she ate. \"If,\" says ",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Brown",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", \"they had worked it right and kept her on her food, she might have been alive yet. She was about 45 or 50 when we found her.\" But she was supplied to her heart's content with green corn, melons, pumpkins and squash, and after the brief enjoyment of a new, strange life to her for a month or five weeks she sickened and died.",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          6
        ]
      }
    ]
  ]
}